## Landing page
landing.heading=Enrol with the safety & security service
landing.fromJanuary=From 1 January 2021
landing.tradersWhoSubmit=Traders who submit Entry Summary Declarations (ENS) using third party software will need to enrol with the Safety & Security (S&S) service.
landing.coms=S&S handles digital communications between customs administrators and carriers or their appointed representatives.
landing.incorporates=S&S incorporates the:
landing.incorporates.1=lodging, handling and processing of an ENS in advance of the arrival of goods into the UK from outside the UK
landing.incorporates.2=issuing of a Movement Reference Number (MRN)
landing.csp=Community System Providers
landing.ifYouAreACsp=If you are a Community System Provider you don’t need to enrol with S&S to submit an ENS.
landing.beforeYouStart.heading=Before you enrol
landing.youNeed=You’ll need:
landing.youNeed.1.1=a
landing.youNeed.1.2=Government Gateway user ID and password
landing.youNeed.1.3=- if you do not have a user ID, you can create one when you apply
landing.youNeed.2.1=an EORI number that starts with GB -
landing.youNeed.2.2=apply for a new one
landing.youNeed.2.3=if yours does not start with GB
landing.takesMinutes=It takes around n minutes to apply to enrol with S&S. You should get a decision immediately.
landing.start=Start now
landing.dontNeedToEnrol=I don’t need to enrol with S&S
landing.welsh.para.1=The online service is also available in
landing.welsh.linkText=Welsh (Cymraeg)

